<font color="#FF0000">PRECISE LANDING FINESSE!</font><br>
<tt>Mon Nov 17  9:36:44 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Never did wear a parachute when I flew Hueys in Nam.. Just wore my stainless steel jock strap, camo paint, P-38 and a light coat of oil.  When I was packing Donut Dollies, I put on my Tiger Stripe lion cloth (modesty) and splashed on some insect repellent (like Cookie says, &quot;A guy's gotta smell good..sometimes!)<br>
When I was shot out of the sky...didn't need no stinking parachute...just crawled out onto the tail boom and lit a Camel cigarette.  About three feet before impact, I would casually step off.  No sweat!  Except the time I stepped on a Marine hiding in the grass.  Boy was he angry.  He was filling out his promotion papers...said that I made him color outside the lines.<br>
Bottom line...I guess PLFs are kinda like aircraft landings...any one that you can walk away from is a good one!<br>
Hang Tough Grunts, God loves you..so do I...but Mom don't!<br><br>
MTF<br><br>
P.S.  Sombody get the air pump...John's starting to wrinkle!<br><br>
Question: What do you get when you cross a Paratrooper, a Jet Jockey, a Marine, a Grunt and an Artillery man?<br>
Answer:  A bunch of duds that keep landing in the wrong places!
<p><code>-- I'm mad...  (Not telling!) </code><p>


